turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort.  You accepted presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Only a trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I remember it well, covered in diamonds in the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, not at all.  I-I still have it.  I wear it quite often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You worked the whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit that he was in love with you, wasn't he?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: maybe just a little, but--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You let him kiss you.  You said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And what of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, I- he got a lot of pleasure out of it and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, if you hadn't been so nosey and suspicious, you never would have heard about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, that's a nice point of view I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm growing quite tired and bored of this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So am I, bored stiff.  Would you like some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have a little I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want any.  You've already had three glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason, besides, they were very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, it seems silly to go on and on in such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly call three liqueur glasses of brandy in a whole evening going on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's becoming a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand simply because you don't happen to want any at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be so stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Going out somewhere, dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, that reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's the woman's job to allure the man.  Why don't you watch me for a moment?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, that is perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, it's not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, yes it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, Do shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's a pity you didn't take a little more brandy.  It might have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Um, It doesn't seem to have worked such wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, snap, snap, snap like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: adder don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nonsense, they have a little bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care if they bark and roll around like hoops, okay.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: [BREATHING]

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Did you see much of Peter Burden after the divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did quite a bit.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I suppose you let him kiss you a good deal more then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your own business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must have a riotous time, no restraint at all, very enjoyable.  I mean, you never had much anyway.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh dear, you really are becoming quite insufferable.  I would imagine it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm not the least bit drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I mentioned once before that I had only three-minute liqueur glasses of brandy the entire evening long.  A child of two could not be drunk on that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh no, on the contrary, a child of two could get violently drunk on only one glass.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, very interesting.  How about a child of three or a child of six?  How about a child of nine?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, You are so insufferable.  Do you stop.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, This is very interesting.  We- we might get a splendid debate going about this intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny, dear, you better have some more brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, very good idea.  I will.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Ugh.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You better turn that off I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's very late and it will disturb the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There aren't any people upstairs; it's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, there are people downstairs I suppose.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They're away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It is not time of year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Fine, if you insist on being completely insolent.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.  It is driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, do try to control yourself darling.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You really do need to develop uh a clearer head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I- I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda-- Listen- Listen-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I hate you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, no.  I'm tired of listening to you.  You're boorish and idiotic and completely overbearing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very music- amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yeah, very amusing.  Let me go.  I'm getting out of here.  I can't believe I intended to marry you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You are a vile tempered, loose living, wicked little beast, and I never want to set eyes on you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, marry you again?  I must have been insane.  What was I thinking?  I mean, you're completely outrageous.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up, shut up.  I wouldn't marry you again if you came crawling to me on bended knee. You're a mean, evil-minded little vampire and I hope to God I never set eyes on you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Beast; brute; cad; whore
